<task id="task-5022" class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Pull</title><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><context class="- topic/section task/context ">You can use the pull command to incorporate changes from a remote repository into the current
         branch. For more information on the pull command, refer to this Git
         document: <xref href="https://git-scm.com/docs/git-pull" scope="external" class="- topic/xref ">Git pull</xref>.<p class="- topic/p ">Do as follows:</p></context><steps class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the main toolbar, click on <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Git</uicontrol>  dropdown arrow &gt;
                  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Pull</uicontrol>.</cmd><stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult "><p class="- topic/p "><image width="250" href="../Platform-Edition/image/ks-pe-850-pull.png" class="- topic/image "/></p>The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Pull</uicontrol> dialog appears. </stepresult></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select the remote branch to
               be pulled into your local branch.</cmd><stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult "><image width="500" href="../image/ks-840-remote-branch.png" class="- topic/image "/></stepresult></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Finish</uicontrol>.</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Pull Result</uicontrol> dialog displays information about
               pulling requests on the selected branch.</cmd><stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult "><image width="350" href="../image/ks-840-pull-result.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">Pull result dialog</alt></image></stepresult></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">OK</uicontrol> when you finish.</cmd></step></steps></taskbody></task>